# Engineering Principles

## TDD is mandatory

- Red -> Green -> Refactor for every feature and bugfix.
- Start by writing or updating a failing test that proves behavior.
- Implement only the minimum code to pass tests.
- Refactor only after tests are green.
- Do not merge code without relevant automated tests.

## SOLID expectations

- **S**: one reason to change per class/module.
- **O**: extend behavior via composition/abstractions, avoid risky modifications.
- **L**: derived types must preserve parent contracts.
- **I**: prefer focused interfaces over broad ones.
- **D**: depend on abstractions, inject concrete dependencies.

## DRY expectations

- Eliminate repeated business rules, validation logic, and mapping code.
- Extract reusable helpers only after duplication appears in at least two places.
- Keep one canonical source for each domain rule and constant.

## Definition of done

- Tests added/updated first and passing.
- No unnecessary duplication introduced.
- Design choices documented when trade-offs affect SOLID.
